@9:38:06: There is a way to validate not only for a type but also for specific values. In this case the following code will work:

class Vote(BaseModel):
    post_id: int
    dir: int

    @validator('dir')
    def must_be_one_or_zero(cls, value):
        if value not in (0, 1):
            raise ValueError("Must be either 1 or 0")
        return value

the vote schema can be set to validate exclusively 0 or 1 by creating a list of integers 0 and 1 and setting the "dir" attribute to only accept values from that list. That can be done with the code below:
class Vote(BaseModel):
    post_id: int
    dir: int
    @validator('dir')
    def number_must_equal_0_or_1(cls,dir):
        directions=[0,1]

        if dir not in directions:
            raise ValueError(f'Must be either {directions}')
        return dir

